snippet.textDisplay: I am really amazed at the Bangla pronunciation of A.R Rahman. As it is not conventional Bengali language. It's a world-class Bengali poem by Nobel Laureate Rabindranath Tagore. It really needs a strong concentration of a Bengali man to pronounce those words perfectly. Hence, A.R Rahman not being a Bengali man nailed it perfectly. His pronunciation really gives me goosebumps. Found a new taste of Tagore's poem through this song. Hats off to the whole team.

snippet.textDisplay:
Where the mind is without fear and the head is held high
Where knowledge is free
Where the world has not been broken up into fragments
By narrow domestic walls
Where words come out from the depth of truth
Where tireless striving stretches its arms towards perfection
Where the clear stream of reason has not lost its way
Into the dreary desert sand of dead habit
Where the mind is led forward by thee
Into ever-widening thought and action
Into that heaven of freedom, my Father, let my country awake.
